<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>One of the two officers shot during Wednesday night's riots in Louisville has returned to his police  precinct just hours after being released from hospital. </p>

<p>Major Aubrey Gregory was greeted with a round of applause as he showed up to the Louisville Metro Police's roll call on Thursday morning, less than 24 hours after being shot in the hip. </p>

<p>Gregory is the commander of Louisville police department's special operations division and was leading the department's response to riots that erupted in Louisville on Wednesday night following a grand jury's decision not to indict any officers on murder charges over the shooting death of black woman, Breonna Taylor. </p>

<p>Major Aubrey Gregory returned to his the Lousville Metro Police Department Precinct on Thursday morning, less than 24 hours after he was shot during riots over Breonna Taylor </p>

<p>Gregory is the commander of Louisville police department's special operations division</p>
